{{Notability|biographies|date=September 2009}} {{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Girija Keer | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1933 | birth_place = Maharashtra, India | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = Marathi | nationality = Indian | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = Novels, short stories, travelogues, and literature for children | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = Janmathep | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Girija Keer''' (born 1933) is a [[Marathi people|Marathi]] writer from [[Maharashtra, India]].
She started her career as a school teacher in a village.
Keer has written thus far 85 books in Marathi in the fields of novels, short stories, travelogues, and literature for children.
Following a six-year research involving interviews with prisoners undergoing life imprisonment at Yerawada prison near [[Pune]], she recently published a book titled ''Janmathep'' (जन्मठेप).
Keer has received some awards for her works.{{Specify|date=September 2009}}
