{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} '''S. Morris Engel''' (born 1931) is an author, philosopher, and [[linguistics|linguist]]. He received his PhD from the [[University of Toronto]] in 1959, writing on "''The philosophy of [[language]] in [[Thomas Hobbes|Hobbes]] and [[John Locke|Locke]]''".<ref>{{cite journal |last= Engel|first= S Morris|title= The philosophy of language in Hobbes and Locke: a comparative study|publisher= Thesis, PhD|year= 1959|oclc= 222042217 }}</ref> He was a professor of philosophy at the [[University of Southern California]] and [[York University]].
==Published works== *''Analyzing Informal Fallacies'' *''Fallacies and Pitfalls of Language: The Language Trap'' *''Language and Illumination: Studies in the History of Philosophy'' *''The Chain of Logic'' *''The Language Trap: Or, How to Defend Yourself Against the Tyranny of Words'' *''The Problem of Tragedy'' *''The Study of Philosophy'' *''With Good Reason: An Introduction to Informal Fallacies''<ref>{{cite book |title= With good reason: an introduction to informal fallacies|last= Engel|first= S Morris|year= 2000|edition= 6th.|publisher= [[Bedford-St. Martin's]]|location= Boston|isbn= 978-0-312-15758-6|oclc= 43027353}}</ref> *''[[Ludwig Wittgenstein|Wittgenstein's]] Doctrine of the Tyranny of Language: An Historical and Critical Examination of His Blue Book''
Engel also translated ''"Cat in the Ghetto: Stories"'' by Rachmil Bryks from [[Yiddish]] to English.<ref>{{cite book |title= A cat in the ghetto: four novelettes|last= Bryks|first= Rachmil|others= Engel, S Morris (trans.)|year= 1959|publisher= [[Bloch Publishing Company]]|location= New York City|oclc= 4061285}} Also {{OCLC|234178313}} Recent ({{As of|2008|lc=on}}) edition published as {{cite book |title= A cat in the ghetto: stories|last= Bryks|first= Rachmil|others= Engel, S Morris (trans.)|year= 2008|edition= 1st.|publisher= Persea Books|location= New York City|isbn= 978-0-89255-327-3|oclc= 173243756}}</ref>
